Class DistributedDataSet

  • java.lang.Object
    • oracle.spatial.hadoop.vector.data.SimpleInputDataSet
      • oracle.spatial.hadoop.vector.data.FileInputDataSet
        • oracle.spatial.hadoop.vector.data.SpatialIndexInputDataSet
          • oracle.spatial.hadoop.vector.InputDataSet
            • oracle.spatial.hadoop.vector.DistributedDataSet
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ConfigurationStorable, AbstractInputDataSet, IODataSet

    public class DistributedDataSet
extends InputDataSet
    A validated, normalized and ready to be distributed version of InputDataSet. An instance of this type is expected to have all the information needed to read and parse the data set it represents.
    A distributed data set has a unique id so it can be identified along a job life cycle.
    Author:
    hsaucedo
